resamd:
1. open amd from desktop
2. open settings in the top right
3. go to display
4. go to custom resolutions and press create new
5. create your new resolution and save
The new res should now show up in game
Courtesy of: **nox#3761**

mmr: The MMR system is still in testing, it may be reset during Early Access. It's currently purely for Dids to look at and see how everything is playing out. Don't take it too seriously and just have fun :D
blackbars:
**Fix Black Bars:**
1. Open "Nvidia Control Panel"
2. "Adjust Desktop Size and Position"
3. Select "Full-Screen"
price: The current price of the game is $13, if you don't agree with the price, then don't buy the game. Or you can wait for a sale :)
projectilepath:
You can enable Predicted Projectile Paths in settings:
Gameplay > Projectiles > Show Predicted Projectile Path
reshade: No, reshade will not get you banned and is allowed by Dids
free: “The goal is to move the game to a free to play model after leaving early access, with a battle pass and more cosmetics. There will be no pay to win mechanics implemented.”
mute:
**How to mute a player:**
- open the scoreboard and press the middle mouse button
- then click the dropdown next to the players name
leftgame: You will gain mmr if an enemy leaves early at any point, it counts as a win. You will also lose mmr if you leave the game at any point, it counts as a loss. You will not see your mmr gain/loss in the menu instantly because the game has not ended on the server yet.
